      // 🔥 FAQ
      'faq_q1': 'How to add a product to the fridge?', 'faq_a1': 'On the main screen, tap the green "+" button in the bottom right corner. You can enter the name manually or use the barcode scanner button.',
      'faq_q2': 'How does the receipt scanner (AI) work?', 'faq_a2': 'This feature is available for Family MAX subscribers. Tap the receipt icon in the top left corner, take a photo of your grocery receipt. Our AI will automatically recognize all products, their quantities, and even suggest approximate expiration dates!',
      'faq_q3': 'How to generate a recipe?', 'faq_a3': 'On the main screen, select one or more products (tap them so they highlight in green). A large orange "Cook" button will appear at the bottom. Tap it, choose your diet type, and AI will generate 5 unique recipes using those products.',
      'faq_q4': 'What happens when a product expires?', 'faq_a4': 'The app will send you a notification a day before the expiration and on the exact day. If the product expires, it automatically moves to the "Trash Bin" so you know exactly what went bad.',
      'faq_q5': 'How to restore a product from the trash bin?', 'faq_a5': 'Tap the red bin icon (Trash) in the top right corner of the main screen. Find the product, tap the three dots next to it, and select "Restore" (to put it back in the fridge) or "To Shopping List".',
      'faq_q6': 'How to create a family and why do I need it?', 'faq_a6': 'Family allows you to synchronize your fridge, shopping lists, and chat with your loved ones (available in Family MAX). Go to "My Profile" -> "My Family" -> "Create family". You will receive a unique code to share with others.',
      'faq_q7': 'How to share a recipe?', 'faq_a7': 'Open a saved or newly generated recipe. In the top right corner, tap the "Share" icon (paper plane). You can send it to the internal family chat or to other apps (Telegram, WhatsApp, etc.).',
      'faq_q8': 'What is Eco-Statistics?', 'faq_a8': 'In the Profile tab, there is a statistics section. It shows your efficiency: how many products you "Saved" (marked as eaten) compared to "Wasted" (moved to trash). The less you throw away, the higher your rating!',
      'faq_q9': 'How does the family chat work?', 'faq_a9': 'After creating or joining a family, a Chat tab will appear at the bottom of the main screen. There you can communicate with your family, send voice messages, photos, files, create polls, and discuss recipes.',
      'faq_q10': 'Why is a product not found via barcode?', 'faq_a10': 'The barcode database (OpenFoodFacts) is community-driven. If a product is missing, the scanner will notify you, and you can simply add it manually.',
      'faq_q11': 'How to change the app language?', 'faq_a11': 'Go to the "My Profile" tab, find the "Language" option, and choose one of the 5 available languages. The app will update immediately.',
      'faq_q12': 'How to cancel a subscription?', 'faq_a12': 'Subscriptions are managed by the app store (Google Play or App Store). Go to "My Profile" -> "Manage Subscription" (or tap it on the Premium screen), and you will be redirected to your phone\'s settings to cancel it.',
